    "plan_content": "## Implementation Plan: `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\nHere's the full plan for adding `Bun.INI` with `parse` and `stringify`, following the exact same pattern as `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.YAML`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### Architecture (same 5-layer pattern as existing formats)\n\n```\nBun.INI.parse(str) / Bun.INI.stringify(obj)\n  ↓ src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig      (JS bindings)\n  ↓ src/interchange/ini.zig           (core INI parser → Expr tree)\n  ↓ BunObject+exports.h               (C++ macro: extern \"C\" + wrap_INI)\n  ↓ BunObject.cpp                     (bunObjectTable entry)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3 New Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/interchange/ini.zig` | Self-contained INI parser → `bun.ast.Expr`. No `DotEnv` dependency. Handles `[sections]`, `key=value`, `;`/`#` comments, type coercion, `key[]` arrays |\n| `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | `create()`, `parse()` (TOMLObject pattern: ArenaAllocator + printJSON + toJSByParseJSON), `stringify()` (YAMLObject pattern: JSPropertyIterator + StringBuilder, emits globals first then `[section]` blocks) |\n| `test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts` | Parse/stringify tests including sections, comments, booleans, numbers, arrays, roundtrip |\n\n### 6 Modified Files\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/interchange.zig` | Add `pub const ini = @import(\"./interchange/ini.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | Add lazy property decl, `@export`, getter fn `getINIObject`, import `INIObject` |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER` (auto-generates the C++ `extern \"C\"` decl and `BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI` wrapper) |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add table row: `INI  BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI  DontDelete|PropertyCallback` |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI` with `parse(input: string): object` and `stringify(input: object): string` |",
